In skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onion, celery, bell pepper and parsley; saute for 4 minutes stirring occasionally. Stir in pecans, stuffing mix, water (according to package directions) and avocado. Grease a 1-quart casserole and spoon in stuffing. Bake in preheated 350 degrees F oven for 20 to 25 minutes until top is lightly browned and stuffing is heated through. Serve.